1 February 1990 saw the release of iconic freedom fighter Mandela after a heroic 27-years behind bars. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa delivered an address following the 30th anniversary of former president Nelson Mandela's speech. 11 February 1990 saw the release of iconic freedom fighter Mandela after a heroic 27-years behind bars. WATCH: 30 years since Mandela's release from prison This year marks the 30th anniversary of when Mandela stepped out of the Victor Verster prison now known as the Drakenstein Correctional Centre. Ramaphosa will deliver the speech at the balcony of the Cape Town city hall.